description:
**About us** :


The Commonwealth Bank of Australia is Australia’s leading provider of integrated financial services including retail, business and institutional banking, funds management, life insurance, superannuation and general insurance.


Coverage in Institutional Banking and Markets (IB&M) is responsible for managing the Group's relationships with major corporate and government clients and institutional investors, and provides a full range of capital raising and risk management products and services.


IB&M’s purpose is combining global connectivity and capability to build a better Australia. The Institutional Banking and Markets International business offers a range of capital raising, trade finance and risk management products and services to institutional clients through our offices in New Zealand, USA, Europe and Asia.


You are a dynamic Executive Assistant working in the Banking Industry.


We are a globally recognised and an innovative thinking Bank.


Together we achieve great things!


**Do work that matters** :


You will provide high-level administrative and business support to the Executive Directors (EDs) of the Coverage teams, to maximise their effectiveness on a day-to-day basis.


Your main responsibilities will include but are not limited to:


* Extensive and effective diary management;
* Effective and accurate travel and logistics (end to end itineraries);
* Effective management of expenses by enforcement of Group expense policy, accurate processing of expense reports and gifts /entertainment registry submission;
* Document management and maintenance of e-files, documents, share point files;
* Complete timely required Compliance and HR procedures of the EDs;
* Troubleshoot internal systems, desktop applications and procedures;
* Special projects e.g. coordination of events, projections, participation in groups as specified by managers.

**We are interested in hearing from you if you have** :


* Minimum 2 years experience as an Administrative Assistant assisting senior stakeholders within the Banking Industry;
* Exceptional written and oral communication skills;
* Proficient Microsoft Office skills;
* Excellent organizational skills and attention to detail;
* Self-motivated and proactive style combined with high discretion and confidentiality;
* Flexibility and adaptability to juggle a range of different tasks within deadlines.

The salary range for this role is from $70,000 to $85,000. The salary may vary based upon several factors including, but not limited to, relevant skills/experience, time in role, base salary of internal peers, prior performance, business line, and geographic/office location.


In order to be considered please indicate your salary expectations on the application form.


If you're already part of the Commonwealth Bank Group (including Bankwest, x15ventures), you'll need to apply through Sidekick to submit a valid application. We’re keen to support you with the next step in your career.


We're aware of some accessibility issues on this site, particularly for screen reader users. We want to make finding your dream job as easy as possible, so if you require additional support please contact HR Direct on 1800 989 696.


Advertising End Date: 28/08/2024
